eporter_agreed_on_going_public_at":"2018-09-18T14:28:26.149Z","team_member_agreed_on_going_public_at":"2021-07-31T00:20:32.611Z","comments_closed?":false,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"hi team,\n\nI'm starting my research on snapchat by scanning all sub-domains on all the domains in-scope: snapchat.com, bitmoji.com, etc.\n\nLet's look at one of the urls, [https://rendering-service.prod.us-east.bitstrips.com/](https://rendering-service.prod.us-east.bitstrips.com/)\n\nWhen I request `GET https://rendering-service.prod.us-east.bitstrips.com/`\nThe response is  `403 Forbidden`\n\nAfter searching, I've found [/WEB-INF/](https://rendering-service.prod.us-east.bitstrips.com/WEB-INF/) \u0026 [/META-INF/](https://rendering-service.prod.us-east.bitstrips.com/META-INF/) directories, which are accessibles and allow directory listing. \n\nInside `/WEB-INF/` we have all the .class files of bitmoji, we can download all the files.\n\nThen by using a java decompiler such as `procyon-decompiler` we reverse the .class files to make those readable. \n\nbest,\nhermès.\n\n## Impact\n\nSource code leaked","bounty_amount":"1000.0","formatted_bounty":"$1,000","weakness":{"id":89,"name":"Information Exposure Through Directory Listing"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[{"id":250888,"file_name":"Screen_Shot_2018-01-02_at_17.51.06.png","expiring_url":"https://hackerone-us-west-2-production-attachments.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/000/250/888/1d71240950a033a1d3af8b7ed43a329b372d720e/Screen_Shot_2018-01-02_at_17.51.06.png?response-content-disposition=attachment%3B%20filename%3D%22Screen_Shot_2018-01-02_at_17.51.06.png%22%3B%20filename%2A%3DUTF-8%27%27Screen_Shot_2018-01-02_at_17.51.06.png\u0026response-content-type=image%2Fpng\u0026X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256\u0026X-Amz-Credential=ASIAQGK6FURQXDQBYHQF%2F20260429%2Fus-west-2%2Fs3%2Faws4_request\u0026X-Amz-Date=20260429T081441Z\u0026X-Amz-Expires=3600\u0026X-Amz-Securi